Noxious Foe
description:
Noxious Foe is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill an aberrant spectre. Killing deviant spectres in the Catacombs of Kourend do not count towards this task.
This achievement requires 60 Slayer to complete. Boosts can be used.

name: Barrows Novice
description:
Barrows Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to open the Barrows chest 10 times.
Completion of the quest Priest in Peril is required to complete this task, as this quest is required to enter Morytania.

name: Defence? What Defence?
description:
Defence? What Defence? is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill any Barrows brother using only magic damage.
Completion of the quest Priest in Peril is required to complete this task, as this quest is required to enter Morytania.

name: Big, Black and Fiery
description: Big, Black and Fiery is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a black dragon. While the King Black Dragon and brutal black dragons count towards this task, baby black dragons do not.

name: The Demonic Punching Bag
description:
The Demonic Punching Bag is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a bloodveld or Mutated Bloodveld.
A Slayer level of 50 is required to damage bloodvelds. Boosts can be used.

name: Preparation Is Key
description: Preparation Is Key is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta without suffering any poison damage.

name: Fighting as Intended II
description: Fighting as Intended II is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta on a free to play world.

name: Bryophyta Novice
description: Bryophyta Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta and loot her chest with a mossy key once. The regular strategies can be followed to complete this task.

name: Protection from Moss
description:
This article contains Combat Achievements that can be completed on free-to-play worlds.
Players without membership cannot claim any rewards or fully complete any tier of the achievements.

name: A Slow Death
description: A Slow Death is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta with either poison or venom being the final source of damage.

name: Deranged Archaeologist Novice
description: Deranged Archaeologist Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist 10 times.

name: The Walking Volcano
description: The Walking Volcano is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a fire giant.

name: Giant Mole Novice
description: Giant Mole Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole 10 times.

name: Not So Great After All
description:
This article contains Combat Achievements that can be completed on free-to-play worlds.
Players without membership cannot claim any rewards or fully complete any tier of the achievements.

name: A Greater Foe
description:
A Greater Foe is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a greater demon.
Killing a greater demon in the Wilderness Slayer Cave does not count for this achievement.

name: A Demon's Best Friend
description: The Skeleton Hellhound is a monster summoned by Vanstrom Klause during the In Search of the Myreque quest to kill the remaining Myreque members. In order for the quest to be completed, the Skeleton Hellhound must be defeated, which should not be a problem for a moderately levelled player, as it is fairly weak. Although it is a skeleton, it does not count as undead, so Crumble Undead does not work against this monster, as well as the salve amulet. Defeating the Skeleton Hellhound will not count for the easy combat achievement...

name: King Black Dragon Novice
description: King Black Dragon Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 10 times.

name: Shayzien Protector
description: Shayzien Protector is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a lizardman shaman in Molch which has not dealt damage to anyone, excluding the damage that its spawns deal.

name: A Scaley Encounter
description: A Scaley Encounter is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Lizardman Shaman.

name: Into the Den of Giants
description: Into the Den of Giants is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a hill giant, moss giant, and a fire giant in the Giants' Den within the Shayzien region.

name: Fighting as Intended
description: Easy Combat Achievements tasks do not require any significant skill levels to complete, typically involving tasks to kill a low amount of a boss or basic tasks involving killing a monster in a specific manner.

name: Sleeping Giant
description: Sleeping Giants is a quest accompanying the Giants' Foundry minigame. The player assists Kovac the giant in investigating an ancient workshop beneath the Giants' Plateau seemingly built by giants, for giants.

name: Obor Novice
description: Obor Novice is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill Obor once and then loot his chest.

name: Sarachnis Novice
description: Sarachnis Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis 10 times.

name: Scurrius Novice
description: Scurrius Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Scurrius once.

name: Sit Rat
description: Sit Rat is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius with a ratbane weapon in a private instance.

name: Calm Before the Storm
description: Calm Before the Storm is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to repair either a mast or a totem pole.

name: Master of Buckets
description: Master of Buckets is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to extinguish at least 5 fires during a single Tempoross fight.

name: Tempoross Novice
description: Tempoross Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross 5 times.

name: Fire in the Hole!
description: Fire in the Hole! is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to attack Tempoross from both sides by loading both cannons on both ships.

name: Mummy!
description: Mummy! is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to heal a pyromancer with a rejuvenation potion after they have fallen.

name: Handyman
description: Handyman is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to repair a brazier which has been destroyed by the Wintertodt.

name: Cosy
description: Cosy is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt with four pieces of warm equipment equipped.

name: Wintertodt Novice
description: Wintertodt Novice is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt 5 times.

name: A Slithery Encounter
description: A Slithery Encounter is an easy combat achievement which requires the player to kill a wyrm. Killing a wyrmling will not count for this combat achievement.

name: Elemental Company
description: Elemental Company is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without attacking the ice or fire elemental.

name: Let them fight
description: Let them fight is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans while having them kill at least 10 ice or fire elementals.

name: One by one
description: One by one is an easy combat achievement requiring the player to kill one of the Royal Titans at a time, without attacking the other.

Amoxliatl Champion
description: Amoxliatl Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl once.

name: Temotli Triumph
description: Temotli Triumph is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl using only glacial temotli as a weapon.

name: Barrows Champion
description: Barrows Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Barrows chest 25 times.

name: Can't Touch Me
description:
Can't Touch Me is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dharok, Verac, Torag, and Guthan without letting them attack the player with melee.
If you have killed 0 of the brothers and get hit by the first brother you try to kill, leaving and re-entering the crypt will NOT reset the task, so you will need to open the chest and start over.
After killing the 4 brothers without being hit, the combat achievement will not unlock until after opening the chest.

name: Pray for Success
description: Pray for Success is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill all six Barrows Brothers and loot the Barrows chest without taking any damage from any of the brothers.

name: Brutal, Big, Black and Firey
description: Brutal, Big, Black and Firey is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a brutal black dragon. A Slayer level of 77 is required to damage a brutal black dragon.

name: Quick Cutter
description: Quick Cutter is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill all 3 of Bryophyta's growthlings within 3 seconds of the first one dying.

name: Bryophyta Champion
description: Bryophyta Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Bryophyta and loot her chest with a mossy key 5 times.

name: Chaos Fanatic Champion
description: Chaos Fanatic Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic 10 times.

name: Sorry, What Was That?
description: Sorry, What Was That? is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic without anyone being hit by his explosion attack.

name: Mage of the Ruins
description:
Mage of the Ruins is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist with only magical attacks.
Damage inflicted by a ring of recoil or by the special attack of a dragonfire shield also counts as magical for the purpose of this task.

name: Crazy Archaeologist Champion
description: Crazy Archaeologist Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist 10 times.

name: I'd Rather Not Learn
description: I'd Rather Not Learn is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist without anyone being hit by his "Rain of Knowledge" attack.

name: Dagannoth Prime Champion
description: Dagannoth Prime Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime 10 times.

name: Dagannoth Rex Champion
description: Dagannoth Rex Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex 10 times.

name: A Frozen King
description: A Frozen King is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex whilst he is immobilized. Curse spells, grasp spells, and ice spells count towards this achievement.

name: Dagannoth Supreme Champion
description: Dagannoth Supreme Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Supreme 10 times.

name: I'd Rather Be Illiterate
description: I'd Rather Be Illiterate is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist without anyone being hit by his "Learn to Read" attack.

name: Deranged Archaeologist Champion
description: Deranged Archaeologist Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist 25 times.

name: Mage of the Swamp
description:
Mage of the Swamp is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Deranged Archaeologist with only magical attacks.
Damage inflicted by a ring of recoil or by the special attack of a dragonfire shield also counts as magical for the purpose of this task.

name: A Smashing Time
description: A Smashing Time is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a gargoyle, requiring 75 Slayer in order to be harmed.

name: Giant Mole Champion
description: Giant Mole Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant mole 25 times.

name: Avoiding Those Little Arms
description: Avoiding Those Little Arms is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole without anyone taking damage from her.

name: King Black Dragon Champion
description: King Black Dragon Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 25 times.

name: Hide Penetration
description: Hide Penetration is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the King Black Dragon with a weapon using the stab attack style.

name: Antifire Protection
description: Dragonfire is the fiery breath attack used by most dragons, hence the name. While it can deal considerable damage to unprepared players, the damage may be negated with certain shields, (super) antifire potions and Protect from Magic.

name: Claw Clipper
description: Claw Clipper is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon with the Protect from Melee prayer activated. This combat achievement will only be completed if Protect from Melee is the only activated prayer, so turn off all other prayers before finishing the kill.

name: Master of Broad Weaponry
description:
Master of Broad Weaponry is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a kurask.
Killing a kurask requires level 70 Slayer. Players must also have leaf-bladed weaponry to kill it. This includes broad ammunition and the Magic Dart spell (requiring a Slayer's staff).
Note: The kurask in the southern cave of the Fremennik Slayer Dungeon can only be harmed while on a kurask Slayer task.

name: Lunar Triplet
description: Lunar Triplet is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest after defeating all three Moons in the Moons of Peril.

name: Back to Our Roots
description: Back to Our Roots is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril with a dragon scimitar without leaving Neypotzli.

name: Moons of Peril Speed-Trialist
description:
Moons of Peril Speed-Trialist is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril in one run in under 8 minutes.
The timer begins upon entering the first boss room (the area where players use the statue to enter the boss arena). Importantly, this means supplies collection before fighting the first Moon does not count towards the timer.

name: Perilous Novice
description: Perilous Novice is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest 5 times.

name: Sit Back and Relax
description: Sit Back and Relax is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to deal 100 damage to creatures using undead thralls. This can be accomplished accumulatively across multiple undead thrall casts and multiple enemies.

name: Obor Champion
description:
This article contains Combat Achievements that can be completed on free-to-play worlds.
Players without membership cannot claim any rewards or fully complete any tier of the achievements.

name: Squashing the Giant
description:
This article contains Combat Achievements that can be completed on free-to-play worlds.
Players without membership cannot claim any rewards or fully complete any tier of the achievements.

name: Back to the Wall
description: Back to the Wall is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Obor without being pushed back more than one square by his knockback attack.

name: Newspaper Enthusiast
description: Newspaper Enthusiast is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis with a crush weapon.

name: Sarachnis Champion
description: Sarachnis Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis 25 times.

name: Efficient Pest Control
description: Efficient Pest Control is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill six giant rats in Scurrius' lair in 3 seconds.

name: Scurrius Champion
description: Scurrius Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius 10 times.

name: Perfect Scurrius
description: Perfect Scurrius is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scurrius in a private instance without taking damage from his Tail Swipe and Falling Bricks attacks, whilst praying correctly against his ranged and magic attacks.

name: A Frozen Foe from the Past
wikiTitle: A Frozen Foe from the Past
description: A Frozen Foe from the Past is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill a skeletal wyvern.

name: Demonbane Weaponry
description:
Demonbane Weaponry is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo with a demonbane weapon equipped.
Holy water does not count as a demonbane weapon for the purpose of this achievement.

name: Demonic Weakening
description: Demonic Weakening is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill Skotizo with no altars active.

name: Skotizo Champion
description: Skotizo Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo once.

name: Tempoross Champion
description: Tempoross Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross 10 times.

name: The Lone Angler
description: The Lone Angler is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross alone without getting hit by any fires, torrents or waves.

name: Hueycoatl Champion
description: Hueycoatl Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl once.

name: You're a wizard
description:
You're a wizard is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl using only earth spells. Only the player seeking the achievement must use earth spells; other players fighting the boss can use any gear.

Note that rings of recoil will fail this task; all damage must be done via earth spells.

name: Leaving No One Behind
description: Leaving No One Behind is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt without any of the pyromancers falling. It is only completed if at least 500 points are earned in the fight. This task can often be achieved passively by playing Wintertodt in the official Wintertodt worlds.

name: Can We Fix It?
description: Dwarf Cannon is a short quest about the conflict between the dwarven outpost at the Coal truck mining site and local goblins. The quest provides access to the Dwarf multicannon, a powerful Ranged weapon.

name: Wintertodt Champion
description: Wintertodt Champion is a medium combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt 10 times.

name: Royal Titan Champion
description: Royal Titan Champion is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 10 times.

name: Royal Titan Adept
description: Royal Titan Adept is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 25 times.

name: It takes too long
description: It takes too long is a medium combat achievement requiring the player to kill both the Royal Titans while they are charging up their area attack. Both titans must die during the same charging phase.

Abyssal Adept
description: Abyssal Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire 20 times.

name: Don't Whip Me
description:
Don't Whip Me is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire without being hit by any external tentacles.
This achievement is easily obtained by only attacking the vents after having successfully disoriented the Abyssal Sire with a shadow spell, preferably Shadow Barrage as it is 100% effective. Once the Abyssal Sire roots itself after having reached 200 HP, the player should only stay in the three centremost rows of squares to avoid any damage from the tentacles.

name: They Grow Up Too Fast
description: They Grow Up Too Fast is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Abyssal Sire before any spawns mature into a scion.

name: Don't Stop Moving
description: Don't Stop Moving is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire without taking damage from any miasma pools.

name: Amoxliatl Adept
description: Amoxliatl Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl 20 times.

name: Nagua Negation
description: Nagua Negation is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl without taking any damage.

name: Kemo Makti
description: Kemo Makti is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl 10 times without leaving her chamber.

name: Amoxliatl Speed-Trialist
description: Amoxliatl Speed-Trialist is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl in less than 1 minute.

name: Totally Shattered
description: Totally Shattered is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl without any of her unstable ice shattering.

name: Faithless Crypt Run
description: Faithless Crypt Run is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill all six Barrows Brothers and loot the Barrows chest without ever having more than 0 Prayer points.

name: Just Like That
description: Just Like That is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Karil the Tainted using only damage dealt by special attacks.

name: Callisto Adept
description: Callisto Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Callisto 10 times. Both Callisto and his singles-plus variant Artio kills count towards this task.

name: The Flincher
description:
The Flincher is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental without taking any damage from its attacks.
If any player takes damage from its attacks, everyone involved in the kill will fail.

name: Hoarder
description:
Hoarder is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental without it unequipping any of their items.
Much like The Flincher, if any player has their equipment unequipped, everyone involved in the kill will fail.

name: Chaos Elemental Adept
description: Chaos Elemental Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental 10 times.

name: Chaos Fanatic Adept
description: Chaos Fanatic Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic 25 times.

name: Praying to the Gods
description:
Praying to the Gods is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Fanatic 10 times, without drinking any potion which restores prayer, or leaving the Wilderness. 
Warning: Entering Ferox Enclave will reset the kill count for this combat task. Even though it is technically in the Wilderness, it is not considered wilderness for the purpose of this task. In general, only places where you risk losing items count. 
The altar east of Ferox can be used to recharge prayer, or the Chaos Altar for a...

name: Commander Zilyana Adept
description: Commander Zilyana Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana 50 times.

name: Commander Showdown
description: Commander Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off Commander Zilyana while all of her bodyguards are dead.

name: Crazy Archaeologist Adept
description: Crazy Archaeologist Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crazy Archaeologist 25 times.

name: Dagannoth Prime Adept
description: Dagannoth Prime Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime 25 times.

name: Dagannoth Rex Adept
description: Dagannoth Rex Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex 25 times.

name: Dagannoth Supreme Adept
description: Dagannoth Supreme Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Supreme 25 times.

name: General Graardor Adept
description: General Graardor Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor 50 times.

name: Ourg Freezer
description: Ourg Freezer is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor while he is immobilized.

name: General Showdown
description: General Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off General Graardor whilst all of his bodyguards are dead.

name: Why Are You Running?
description: Why Are You Running? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole without her burrowing more than two times.

name: Whack-a-Mole
description: Whack-a-Mole is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole within 10 seconds of her resurfacing.

name: Grotesque Guardians Adept
description: Grotesque Guardians Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 25 times.

name: Granite Footwork
description: Granite Footwork is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians without taking damage from Dawn's rockfall attack.

name: Don't Look at the Eclipse
description: Don't Look at the Eclipse is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians without taking damage from Dusk's blinding attack.

name: Prison Break
description: Prison Break is a music track that is unlocked during Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire, upon entering the Ghorrock Prison.

name: Static Awareness
description: Static Awareness is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians without being hit by any lightning attacks.

name: Heal No More
description: Heal No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians without letting Dawn receive any healing from her orbs.

name: Hespori Adept
description: Hespori Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori 5 times.

name: Hesporisn't
description:
Hesporisn't is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off the Hespori with a special attack.
Enchanted bolt special effects can trigger this achievement if the bolt effect activates on the last hit, such as Diamond bolts (e). Emerald bolts (e) have the highest chance of activation, making them also effective for this.

name: Weed Whacker
description: Weed Whacker is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill all of the Hespori's flowers within 5 seconds.

name: Demonbane Weaponry II
description: Demonbane Weaponry II is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off K'ril Tsutsaroth with a demonbane weapon.

name: K'ril Tsutsaroth Adept
description: K'ril Tsutsaroth Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth 50 times.

name: Yarr No More
description: Yarr No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for K'ril Tsutsaroth without him using his special attack.

name: Demonic Showdown
description: Demonic Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off K'ril Tsutsaroth whilst all of his bodyguards are dead.

name: Kalphite Queen Adept
description: Kalphite Queen Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen 25 times.

name: Chitin Penetrator
description: Chitin Penetrator is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen while her defence was last lowered by the player.

name: Who Is the King Now?
description: Who Is the King Now? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the King Black Dragon 10 times in a private instance without leaving.

name: Unnecessary Optimisation
description:
Unnecessary Optimisation is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken after killing all four tentacles.
The Enormous Tentacles can be killed before waking the Kraken.

name: Krakan't Hurt Me
description: Krakan't Hurt Me is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 25 times in a private instance without leaving or logging out.

name: Kraken Adept
description: Kraken Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 20 times.

name: Airborne Showdown
description: Airborne Showdown is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to finish off Kree'arra whilst all of his bodyguards are dead.

name: Kree'arra Adept
description: Kree'arra Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra 50 times.

name: Betrayal
description: Betrayal is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon using the associated weapon.

name: Fortified
description: Fortified is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon without consuming any supplies.

name: Moons of Peril Speed-Chaser
description:
Moons of Peril Speed-Chaser is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all three Moons of Peril in one run in under 6 minutes.
The timer begins upon entering the first boss room (the area where players use the statue to enter the boss arena). Importantly, this means supplies collection before fighting the first Moon does not count towards the timer.

name: The Clone Zone
description: The Clone Zone is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Eclipse Moon without attacking her outside of her clone attack.

name: Perilous Dancer
description: Perilous Dancer is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat all the Moons of Peril in one run, while only taking damage from regular attacks.

name: Fat of the Land
description: Fat of the Land is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to defeat 30 Moons of Peril without leaving Neypotzli.

name: Perilous Champion
description:
Perilous Champion is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to open the Lunar Chest 25 times in the Moons of Peril.

If you are solely farming the combat achievement, defeating Eclipse Moon is a quick method of completing it. After defeating Eclipse Moon, you will be teleported into the Blue Moon area with the salamander sites. Run past the salamander sites to the far south-east entrance. Then continue running past the Blood Moon chamber entrance and take a sip of tea from the cooking stove on the way to...

name: Phantom Muspah Adept
description: Phantom Muspah Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah at least once.

name: Ready to Pounce
description: Ready to Pounce is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis without her using her range attack twice in a row.

name: Inspect Repellent
description: Inspect Repellent is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sarachnis without her dealing damage to anyone.

name: I Can't Reach That
description: I Can't Reach That is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia without taking any damage from her.

name: Scorpia Adept
description: Scorpia Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia 10 times.

name: Guardians No More
description: Guardians No More is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia without killing her guardians.

name: Skotizo Adept
description: Skotizo Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo 5 times.

name: Why Cook?
description: Why Cook? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross, getting rewarded with 10 reward permits from a single Tempoross fight.

name: Dress Like You Mean It
description:
Dress Like You Mean It is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue Tempoross while wearing all four pieces of the angler's outfit. Players may mix and match regular angler's outfit pieces with spirit angler's outfit pieces.
The outfit can either be obtained from the Fishing Trawler (15 Fishing minimum) or aerial fishing (43 Fishing and 35 Hunter). However, 34 Fishing is required in order to wear it.

name: I'm your son
description: I'm your son is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl whilst wearing two pieces of Hueycoatl hide armour. Only the player seeking the achievement must do this; other players fighting the boss can use any gear.

name: Hueycoatl Adept
description: Hueycoatl Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl 10 times.

name: Pillar Lover
description: Pillar Lover is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl whilst it is vulnerable.

name: Nightmare Adept
description: Nightmare Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Nightmare once.

name: Theatre of Blood: SM Adept
description: Theatre of Blood: SM Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode 1 time.

name: Confident Raider
description: Confident Raider is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 100 or above.

name: Movin' on up
description: Movin' on up is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 50 or above.

name: Novice Tomb Looter
description: Novice Tomb Looter is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut at any level 25 times.

name: Novice Tomb Explorer
description: Novice Tomb Explorer is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at any level once.

name: Venenatis Adept
description: Venenatis Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Venenatis 10 times. Both Venenatis and her singles-plus variant Spindel kills count towards this task.

name: Vet'ion Adept
description: Vet'ion Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vet'ion 10 times. Both Vet'ion and his singles-plus variant Calvar'ion kills count towards this task.

name: Why Fletch?
description: Why Fletch? is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to subdue the Wintertodt after earning 3000 or more points during the fight.

name: Zulrah Adept
description: Zulrah Adept is a hard combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah 25 times.

name: Royal Titan Speed-Runner
description: Royal Titan Speed-Runner is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans in under 1 minute and 30 seconds.

name: Perfect Royal Titan
description: Perfect Royal Titans is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without getting hit by any avoidable damage.

name: Titan Killer
description: Titan Killer is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans 15 times without anyone leaving the instance. If a player joins the fight, the current streak will be reset to 0. If a player leaves the fight, the task will be failed and a new instance will need to be created.

name: I need room
description: I need room is a hard combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans while extinguishing all fires and melting all icicles before they dissipate naturally.

Respiratory Runner
description:
Respiratory Runner is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire after only stunning him once.
This task fails whenever Sire wakes up from a stun; killing the respiratory systems via safespotting or tanking the tentacles must be done before stunning Sire. Likewise, enough damage to the Sire must be dealt or a shadow spell cast to disorient it exactly once.
Leaving the nexus will fail the achievement attempt unless you don't wake up the Sire.

name: Perfect Sire
description: Perfect Sire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire without taking damage from the external tentacles, miasma pools, explosion or damage from the Abyssal Sire without praying the appropriate protection prayer.

name: Demonic Rebound
description: Demonic Rebound is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to use Vengeance against the Abyssal Sire's explosion attack.

name: Abyssal Veteran
description: Abyssal Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Abyssal Sire 50 times.

name: Alchemical Veteran
description: Alchemical Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 75 times.

name: Without Ralos' Light
description: Without Ralos' Light is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl without losing any prayer points.

name: Amoxliatl Speed-Chaser
description: Amoxliatl Speed-Chaser is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Amoxliatl in less than 30 seconds. You can do this on a slayer task.

name: Relaxxor
description: Relaxxor is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor after destroying six eggs.

name: Araxxor Veteran
description: Araxxor Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 25 times.

name: Araxxor Speed-Trialist
description: Araxxor Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 4 times within 10 minutes.

name: Reflecting on This Encounter
description: Reflecting on This Encounter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a basilisk knight. Basilisk knights are only found in the Jormungand's Prison on the Island of Stone. In order to access the dungeon, the quest Fremennik Exiles must be completed.

name: Callisto Veteran
description: Callisto Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Callisto 20 times. Both Callisto and his singles-plus variant Artio kills count towards this task.

name: Unrequired Antifire
description: Unrequired Antifire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus without taking any damage from her lava pool attacks.

name: Ghost Buster
description: The ghost buster 500, also known as the Phantasmic Destabiliser Mark 500, was created by Professor Oddenstein and used during the 2013 Halloween event in order to defeat poltergeists that possessed toys in Diango's workshop. It started out empty, but could be loaded with several different destabilisers. When loaded with a white destabiliser, shooting a possessed toy would reveal a coloured poltergeist that could then be defeated by loading the corresponding destabiliser and shooting again.

name: Cerberus Veteran
description: Cerberus Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus 75 times.

name: Anti-Bite Mechanics
description: Anti-Bite Mechanics is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus without taking any melee damage.

name: Undying Raid Team
description: Undying Raid Team is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric raid without anyone dying.

name: Together We'll Fall
description: Together We'll Fall is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill all three Vanguards within ten seconds of killing the first one.

name: Shayzien Specialist
description: Shayzien Specialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for a lizardman shaman without taking any damage from them.

name: Redemption Enthusiast
description: Redemption Enthusiast is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to destroy the Abyssal portal without letting Vespula land.

name: Perfectly Balanced
description:
Perfectly Balanced is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Vanguards without them resetting their health.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

name: Mutta-diet
description: Mutta-diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the muttadiles without letting them heal from the meat tree.

name: Kill It with Fire
description:
Kill It with Fire is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish the ice demon off with a fire spell.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

name: Dancing with Statues
description:
Dancing with Statues is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill credit for one of the stone guardians without taking damage from their falling rocks attack.
Use a flinch method to reduce the chances of the guardians attacking. The falling rock attack has a 3x3 AoE centered on the tile it would fall on, so run two spaces away to avoid getting hit.
While regular accounts only need to do more than 50% of the damage to receive kill credit, Ironmen accounts need to do 100% of the damage for...

name: Cryo No More
description:
Cryo No More is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for the Ice Demon without taking any damage.

Iron players must kill the Ice Demon solo to be eligible.
For solo-run attempts, be sure raid scaling is set to "0" for the easiest fight, as scaling a raid to "1" doubles boss health.

name: Chambers of Xeric Veteran
description: Chambers of Xeric Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric 25 times.

name: Blizzard Dodger
description: Blizzard Dodger is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive kill-credit for the Ice Demon without activating the Protect from Range prayer.

name: Dust Seeker
description: Dust Seeker is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a challenge mode Chambers of Xeric run in the targeted time.

name: Chaos Elemental Veteran
description: Chaos Elemental Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Chaos Elemental 25 times.

name: Reminisce
description: Reminisce is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana in a private instance using only melee.

name: Commander Zilyana Veteran
description: Commander Zilyana Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana 100 times.

name: Hot on Your Feet
description: Hot on Your Feet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast without killing or taking damage from the dark energy core.

name: Finding the Weak Spot
description:
Finding the Weak Spot is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish off the Corporeal Beast with a dragon halberd or crystal halberd special attack.
For this task to completed successfully, the halberd has to be using the stab attack style.

name: Corporeal Beast Veteran
description: Corporeal Beast Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast 25 times.

name: Chicken Killer
description: Chicken Killer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast alone.

name: Corrupted Gauntlet Veteran
description: Corrupted Gauntlet Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Corrupted Gauntlet 5 times.

name: 3, 2, 1 - Mage
description: The Crystalline Hunllef is the boss monster within the Gauntlet. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Hunllef.

name: Wolf Puncher
description: Wolf Puncher is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without making more than one attuned weapon within The Gauntlet.

name: Gauntlet Veteran
description: Gauntlet Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Gauntlet 5 times. Completions of the Corrupted Gauntlet will also count towards this task.

name: Egniol Diet
description: Egniol Diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without making an egniol potion, within The Gauntlet.

name: Crystalline Warrior
description: Crystalline Warrior is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef with a full set of perfected crystal armour equipped.

name: 3, 2, 1 - Range
description: The Crystalline Hunllef is the boss monster within the Gauntlet. Its counterpart in the Corrupted Gauntlet is the Corrupted Hunllef.

name: From One King to Another
description:
From One King to Another is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime using a rune thrownaxe special attack, bounced off Dagannoth Rex. 

Ironmen cannot receive help from other players to help tank the Kings.
For the task to count, the special attack must be the last attack made when Prime's death animation finishes.

name: Death to the Seer King
description: Death to the Seer King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Prime whilst under attack by Dagannoth Supreme and Dagannoth Rex.

name: Toppling the Diarchy
description: Echo Dagannoth Rex is a more challenging variant of Dagannoth Rex that was accessible during the Raging Echoes League. To fight the Echo Dagannoth Kings the player must have a Fremennik echo orb, which is dropped by the regular Dagannoth Kings, in their inventory. The kings share a health bar of 1800. During the fight, two of them will use protection prayers against all styles. It is best to damage the king with no overheads. After a certain amount of damage poison will scatter over random tiles and the kings will rotate...

name: Death to the Warrior King
description: Death to the Warrior King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Rex whilst under attack by Dagannoth Supreme and Dagannoth Prime.

name: Rapid Succession
description: Echo Dagannoth Rex is a more challenging variant of Dagannoth Rex that was accessible during the Raging Echoes League. To fight the Echo Dagannoth Kings the player must have a Fremennik echo orb, which is dropped by the regular Dagannoth Kings, in their inventory. The kings share a health bar of 1800. During the fight, two of them will use protection prayers against all styles. It is best to damage the king with no overheads. After a certain amount of damage poison will scatter over random tiles and the kings will rotate...

name: Death to the Archer King
description: Death to the Archer King is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Dagannoth Supreme whilst under attack by Dagannoth Prime and Dagannoth Rex.

name: If Gorillas Could Fly
description: If Gorillas Could Fly is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a demonic gorilla.

name: Hitting Them Where It Hurts
description: Hitting Them Where It Hurts is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to finish off a demonic gorilla with a demonbane weapon.

name: Exposed Doom
description: Exposed Doom is an elite combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl during its melee charge phase at any delve level.

name: Doom Crawler
description: Doom Crawler is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 1 in less than 30 seconds.

name: Doom Adept
description: Doom Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 3.

name: Duke Sucellus Speed-Trialist
description: Duke Sucellus Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus in under 1 minute, without a slayer task.

name: Duke Sucellus Adept
description: Duke Sucellus Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus once after completion of Desert Treasure II.

name: I was here first!
description: I was here first! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a jaguar warrior using a claw-type weapon special attack.

name: Furball
description: Furball is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete wave 4 of the Fortis Colosseum without taking avoidable damage from a manticore.

name: Denied
description: Denied is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete wave 7 without the minotaur ever healing other enemies.

name: Fragment of Seren Speed-Trialist
description: Fragment of Seren Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement that requires the Fragment of Seren boss fight to be completed in less than four minutes. Completion of Song of the Elves is required to attempt this achievement as the fight during the quest does not count. The fight can be attempted at the Memoriam Device in Prifddinas.

name: Galvek Speed-Trialist
description:
Galvek Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Galvek in less than 3 minutes. The fight can be attempted at the Pool of Dreams to the east on the Myths' Guild's ground floor.
The player must deal 1200 damage to Galvek in 300 ticks, or 49 possible Dragon hunter crossbow (Rapid) attacks averaging 24.48 damage per attack.

name: Ourg Freezer II
description: Ourg Freezer II is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor without him attacking any players.

name: General Graardor Veteran
description: General Graardor Veteran is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill General Graardor 100 times.

name: Hard Hitter
description: Hard Hitter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Giant Mole within four hits that deal damage.

name: Glough Speed-Trialist
description: Glough Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Glough in less than 2 minutes and 30 seconds. The fight can be attempted at the burning brazier in Zooknock's house.

name: Perfect Grotesque Guardians
description:
Perfect Grotesque Guardians is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians whilst completing the Don't Look at the Eclipse, Prison Break, Granite Footwork, Heal No More, Static Awareness, and Done before Dusk tasks.
This means the player must kill the Grotesque Guardians without doing the following:

Taking damage from Dusk's blinding attack.
Taking damage from Dusk's prison attack.
Taking damage from Dawn's rockfall attack.
Letting Dawn receive any healing from her orbs.
Being...

name: Grotesque Guardians Veteran
description: Grotesque Guardians Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 50 times.

name: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Trialist
description: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians in 2:00 or less. Despite the official description, a time of exactly 2:00.00 will count for the achievement.

name: From Dusk...
description: From Dusk... is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 10 times without leaving the instance.

name: Done before Dusk
description: Done before Dusk is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians before Dusk uses his prison attack for a second time.

name: Plant-Based Diet
description: Plant-Based Diet is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori without losing any prayer points.

name: Hespori Speed-Trialist
description: Hespori Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori in 48 seconds or less.

name: The Bane of Demons
description: The Bane of Demons is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat K'ril Tsutsaroth in a private instance using only demonbane spells.

name: K'ril Tsutsaroth Veteran
description: K'ril Tsutsaroth Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth 100 times.

name: Demonic Defence
description: Demonic Defence is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth in a private instance without taking any of his melee hits.

name: Prayer Smasher
description: Prayer Smasher is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen using only Verac's flail as a weapon. Inflicting recoil damage with a ring of recoil, ring of suffering, echo boots, or Vengeance is not allowed. This has to be done solo; damage from another player will invalidate the kill even if they are also using a flail. However, damage from thralls and poison inflicted via the serpentine helm are allowed, and the kill can be completed over several trips.

name: Kalphite Queen Veteran
description: Kalphite Queen Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen 50 times.

name: Insect Deflection
description:
Insect Deflection is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kalphite Queen by using the Vengeance spell as the finishing blow.
Another account can cast Vengeance Other on the player and it will count toward this combat achievement.

name: Ten-tacles
description: Ten-tacles is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken 50 times in a private instance without leaving or logging out.

name: Kree'arra Veteran
description: Kree'arra Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra 100 times.

name: Leviathan Speed-Trialist
description: Leviathan Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan in under 1 minute and 50 seconds, without being on a slayer task.

name: Leviathan Adept
description: Leviathan Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan once after completion of Desert Treasure II.

name: High Hitter
description:
High Hitter is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat a Moon before they start their second special attack.
This combat achievement does not count special attacks that are happening as you enter the room, so players struggling with this task may wish to enter shortly after a special starts, to give them more time.

name: Nex Veteran
description: Nex Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex once.

name: Nex Survivors
description: Nex Survivors is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex without having anyone die during the fight.

name: Versatile Drainer
description: Versatile Drainer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to drain the Phantom Muspah's prayer with three different sources in one kill.

name: Phantom Muspah Veteran
description: Phantom Muspah Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah 25 times.

name: Phantom Muspah Speed-Trialist
description: Phantom Muspah Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah in less than 3 minutes without a Slayer task.

name: Can't Escape
description:
Can't Escape is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah without running.
This achievement fails as soon as the player either leaves the starting tile with Run on, or turns Run on at any point during the fight. Only walking is permissible.

name: Phosani's Veteran
description: Phosani's Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare once.

name: No time to pray
description: No time to pray is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill the Royal Titans without losing any prayer points.

name: Scorpia Veteran
description: Scorpia Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Scorpia 25 times.

name: Up for the Challenge
description: Up for the Challenge is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo, or Awakened Altars without equipping a demonbane weapon.

name: Demon Evasion
description: Demon Evasion is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Skotizo without taking any damage.

name: Perfect Hueycoatl
description: Perfect Hueycoatl is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl perfectly 5 times without leaving. Only the player seeking the achievement must get a perfect kill; other players in the fight do not need to.

name: Hueycoatl Veteran
description: Hueycoatl Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Hueycoatl 25 times.

name: Hueycoatl Speed-Trialist
description: Hueycoatl Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl in 2:30.

name: Mimic Veteran
description:
Mimic Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Mimic once.
In order to be eligible to obtain a Mimic, players must first speak to the strange casket upstairs in Watson's house in Hosidius to enable the chance of a reward casket turning into the Mimic. An elite reward casket has a 1/35 chance of being a mimic, while master reward caskets have a 1/15 chance. There is a one-time guaranteed Mimic encounter on either the 11th master or 26th elite casket, whichever is first.

name: Sleep Tight
description: Sleep Tight is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Nightmare solo.

name: Nightmare Veteran
description: Nightmare Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat The Nightmare 25 times. Phosani's Nightmare kills will also count towards this achievement.

name: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Trialist
description: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Trialist elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare, solo, in under 23 minutes.

name: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Trialist
description: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare in a team of 5 players in under 5 minutes.

name: Explosion!
description: Explosion! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill two Husks at the same time.

name: Theatre of Blood Veteran
description:
Theatre of Blood Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood 25 times. Hard Mode Theatre of Blood completions will also count towards this achievement.
Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode does not count towards the completion of this achievement.

name: They Won't Expect This
description: They Won't Expect This is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode, enter the Pestilent Bloat room from the opposite side.

name: Pass It On
description:
Pass It On is an elite combat achievement which requires the player in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode, to successfully pass on the green ball to a team mate.
The green ball is a special attack launched by Verzik Vitur in her third phase.

name: Nylocas, On the Rocks
description: Nylocas, On the Rocks is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to freeze any 4 nylocas with a single Ice Barrage spell during a Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode raid. As the achievement is completed immediately after freezing 4 nylocas, the raid does not need to be completed.

name: No-Pillar
description: No-Pillar is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to survive Verzik Vitur's pillar phase in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without losing a single pillar.

name: Just To Be Safe
description:
Just To Be Safe is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sotetseg in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode after having split the big ball with your entire team. This must be done with a group size of at least 2.
The big ball refers to the special attack by Sotetseg where it launches a big red ball that cannot be protected against. When multiple players stand on the same tile, the damage inflicted from the ball is split between the players. This attack is used after Sotetseg launches at least ten...

name: Don't Look at Me!
description: Don't Look at Me! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Xarpus in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without him reflecting any damage to anyone.

name: Chally Time
description: Chally Time is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Pestilent Bloat in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode by using a dragon halberd or crystal halberd special attack as your final attack.

name: Attack, Step, Wait
description: Attack, Step, Wait is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to survive Verzik Vitur's second phase in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without anyone getting bounced by Verzik.

name: Appropriate Tools
description:
Appropriate Tools is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Pestilent Bloat in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode with everyone having a salve amulet equipped.
This achievement can be completed with any version of the salve amulet.

name: Anticoagulants
description: Anticoagulants is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Maiden of Sugadinti in the Theatre of Blood: Entry Mode without letting a blood spawn live for more than 10 seconds.

name: Thermonuclear Veteran
description: Thermonuclear Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil 20 times.

name: Spec'd Out
description: Spec'd Out is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil using only special attacks.

name: Hazard Prevention
description: Hazard Prevention is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Thermonuclear Smoke Devil without it hitting anyone.

name: Tomb Explorer
description: Tomb Explorer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid once, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Perfect Het
description: Perfect Het is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Het challenge room without taking any damage from the light beam or orbs, and destroying Het's Seal in one cycle, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Perfect Crondis
description: Perfect Crondis is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Crondis challenge room without letting a crocodile get to the tree, without anyone losing water from their container and in under one minute, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Perfect Apmeken
description: Perfect Apmeken is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Apmeken challenge room in a group of two or more without allowing any dangers to trigger, standing in venom, or being hit by a volatile baboon, while completing the room within three minutes, at raid level 150 or above.

name: No skipping allowed
description: No skipping allowed is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba while only destroying uncracked boulders, without dying, and having the Boulderdash invocation active, at raid level 150 or above.

name: I'm in a rush
description: I'm in a rush is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba after destroying four or fewer rolling boulders in total without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Helpful spirit who?
description: Helpful spirit who? is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid at level 150 or above without relying on the Helpful Spirit for supplies.  The raid must be completed deathless by the entire party and will fail if any players in the raid use supplies from the Helpful Spirit.

name: Hardcore Tombs
description: Hardcore Tombs is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid solo without dying, at level 150 or above. The Hardcore Run invocation does not need to be active in order to complete the achievement.

name: Hardcore Raiders
description: Hardcore Raiders is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid in a group of two or more without anyone dying, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Dropped the ball
description: Dropped the ball is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Akkha without dropping any materialising orbs and without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Down Do Specs
description: Down Do Specs is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Wardens after staggering the boss twice during phase 2 without dying, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Novice Tomb Raider
description: Novice Tomb Raider is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at any level 50 times.

name: Expert Tomb Explorer
description: Expert Tomb Explorer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid once, at level 300 or above.

name: Unending Torment
description:
Unending Torment is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Tormented Demon. 
This achievement will only count as completed for Tormented Demons killed after the completion of While Guthix Sleeps. The two Tormented Demons killed during the quest while player's stats are temporarily increased due to touching the Stone of Jas do not count towards task completion.

name: Two Times the Torment
description: Two Times the Torment is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill two Tormented Demons within two seconds.

name: Through Fire and Flames
description: Through Fire and Flames is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Tormented Demon whilst their fire shield is inactive, which is the duration they throw out the fireballs and stun.

name: Rapid Reload
description: Rapid Reload is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to hit three tormented demons within three seconds using a ballista or crossbow.

name: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Trialist
description: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's first challenge in less than 45 seconds.

name: The II Jad Challenge
description: The II Jad Challenge is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's second challenge.

name: Facing Jad Head-on III
description: Facing Jad Head-on III is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's second challenge with only melee.

name: Half-Way There
description: Half-Way There is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill a Jal-Zek within the Inferno. Jal-Zek is first encountered on wave 35 of the Inferno.

name: Fight Caves Veteran
description: Fight Caves Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves once.

name: Facing Jad Head-on
description: Facing Jad Head-on is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves with only melee weapons equipped. Players are allowed to log out and back into the same world and still be eligible for the combat achievement, but hopping worlds is not allowed.

name: A Near Miss!
description: A Near Miss! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves after surviving a hit from TzTok-Jad without praying.

name: Vardorvis Speed-Trialist
description: Vardorvis Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis in less than 1 minute and 15 seconds without a slayer task.

name: Vardorvis Adept
description: Vardorvis Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis once after completion of the Desert Treasure II quest.

name: Venenatis Veteran
description: Venenatis Veteran is an elite combat achievement requiring the player to kill Venenatis 20 times. Both Venenatis and her singles-plus variant Spindel kills count towards this task.

name: Vet'eran
description: Vet'eran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vet'ion 20 times. Both Vet'ion and his singles-plus variant Calvar'ion kills count towards this task.

name: Zombie Destroyer
description: Zombie Destroyer is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath's zombified spawn without using crumble undead.

name: Vorkath Veteran
description: Vorkath Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath 50 times.

name: Stick 'em With the Pointy End
description: Stick 'em With the Pointy End is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath using melee weapons only.

name: Whisperer Speed-Trialist
description: Whisperer Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer in under 3 minutes without being on a slayer task.

name: Whisperer Adept
description: Whisperer Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer once after completion of the Desert Treasure II quest.

name: Tentacular
description: Tentacular is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer while on the Arceuus spellbook. You can complete this combat achievement with the Whisperer's awakened variant.

name: Yama Speed-Trialist
description: Yama Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama in an average time of under 3:38 over the player's most recent four kills.

name: Yama Adept
description: Yama Adept is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama once.

name: Back so soon?
description: Back so soon? is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without the Judge of Yama being attacked with the wrong style, and without taking more than one instance of damage each time you are exiled from the arena.

name: Zalcano Veteran
description: Zalcano Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano 25 times.

name: The Spurned Hero
description:
The Spurned Hero is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano as the player who has dealt the most damage to her.
The achievement checks for the amount of mining damage dealt to Zalcano after breaking her stone armour, rather than checking whether the player is the MVP for that kill (i.e. the one who receives the infernal ashes upon defeating her).

name: Team Player
description: Team Player is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to receive imbued tephra from a golem.

name: Perfect Zalcano
description: Perfect Zalcano is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zalcano 5 times in a row without leaving or getting hit by the following: Falling rocks, rock explosions, Zalcano powering up, or standing in a red symbol.

name: Zulrah Veteran
description: Zulrah Veteran is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah 75 times.

name: Zulrah Speed-Trialist
description: Zulrah Speed-Trialist is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah in less than 1 minute 20 seconds, without a slayer task.

name: Snake. Snake!? Snaaaaaake!
description: Snake. Snake!? Snaaaaaake! is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill 3 snakelings simultaneously while fighting Zulrah.

name: Snake Rebound
description: Snake Rebound is an elite combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah by using the Vengeance spell as the finishing blow.

name: Get 3 new uniques from easy clues
Get 3 new uniques from easy clues
Get 3 new uniques from easy clues
Get 3 new uniques from easy clues

Get 3 new uniques from medium clues

Get 3 new uniques from medium clues
