wikiTitle: Money making guide/Killing the Corporeal Beast

name: Get 1 unique from Doom of Mokhaiotl
Don't Flame Me
description: Don't Flame Me is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its flame wall attack.

name: The Flame Skipper
description:
The Flame Skipper is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without letting it spawn a flame wall attack.
This achievement will only count as completed if the Hydra does not reach the middle and stop moving before changing phases.

name: Unrequired Antipoisons
description: Unrequired Antipoisons is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its acid pool attack.

name: Mixing Correctly
description: Mixing Correctly is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without empowering it.

name: Alcleanical Hydra
description: Alcleanical Hydra is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without taking any damage.

name: Alchemical Speed-Chaser
description: Alchemical Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra in under 1 minute and 45 seconds.

name: Lightning Lure
description: Lightning Lure is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra without being hit by its lightning attack.

name: Working Overtime
description: Working Overtime is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 15 times without leaving the room.

name: Alchemical Master
description: Alchemical Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra 150 times.

name: Araxxor Speed-Chaser
description: Araxxor Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 5 times in 10:00.

name: Perfect Araxxor
description: Perfect Araxxor is a master combat achievement requiring the player to perfectly kill Araxxor.

name: Arachnid Lover
description: Arachnid Lover is a master combat achievement requiring the player to kill Araxxor 10 times without leaving his lair.

name: Araxyte Betrayal
description: Araxyte Betrayal is a master combat achievement which requires the player to have an araxyte kill three other araxytes.

name: Let it seep in
description: Let it seep in is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor without ever having venom immunity. Despite the task's description, poison immunity will not disqualify the player from completing the achievement.

name: Araxxor Master
description: Araxxor Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 75 times.

name: Arooo No More
description: Arooo No More is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus without her summoning any Summoned Souls during the battle.

name: Cerberus Master
description: Cerberus Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Cerberus 150 times.

name: Chambers of Xeric Master
description: Chambers of Xeric Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric 75 times.

name: No Time for Death
description: No Time for Death is a master combat achievement which requires the player to clear the tightrope room without killing any of the deathly mages or rangers.

name: Undying Raider
description:
Undying Raider is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric solo raid without dying.
The task can be completed alongside Undying Raid Team.

name: Chambers of Xeric (Solo) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric (Solo) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric solo run within 21 minutes.

name: Perfect Olm (Trio)
description:
Perfect Olm (Trio) is a master combat achievement which requires the team to kill the Great Olm without taking damage from his crystal burst, teleport, fire wall, healing pool, crystal bomb, and prayer orb attacks. The player must also not let his hands regenerate during phase 3 and not take consecutive damage from the same acid pool.
Duo Group Ironmen are not required to do this task, as they would lose prestige status.
To do this in a solo raid, set scaling to 2. In a duo, set it to 1.

name: Putting It Olm on the Line
wikiTitle: Putting It Olm on the Line
description:
Putting It Olm on the Line is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a solo Chambers of Xeric raid with 40,000 or more points.
Challenge Mode cannot be used for this task.

name: Playing with Lasers
description:
Playing with Lasers is a master combat achievement which requires the player to clear the Crystal Crabs without wasting a single orb after activating the first crystal.
This task is best completed in a group as solo encounters require the player to bind the crabs in place repeatedly with a hammer and the layout of the room may be unfeasible for completing it.

name: Chambers of Xeric (Trio) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric (Trio) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a trio-scaled Chambers of Xeric in under 16:30.

name: A Not So Special Lizard
description: A Not So Special Lizard is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Great Olm in a solo raid without letting him use any of the following special attacks in his second to last phase: Crystal Burst, Lightning Walls, Teleportation Portals or left-hand autohealing.

name: Anvil No More
description: Anvil No More is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Tekton before he is able to use the anvil a second time.

name: Stop Drop and Roll
description: Stop Drop and Roll is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vasa Nistirio before he performs his teleport attack for the second time.

name: Blind Spot
description: Blind Spot is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Tekton without taking any damage.

name: Perfect Olm (Solo)
description: Perfect Olm (Solo) is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Great Olm without taking damage from his crystal burst, teleport, fire wall, healing pool, crystal bomb and prayer orb attacks. The player must also not let his hands regenerate during phase 3 and not take consecutive damage from the same acid pool.

name: Chambers of Xeric (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric (5-scale) in under 15:00.

name: Immortal Raider
description:
Immortal Raider is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a solo Challenge Mode Chambers of Xeric without dying.
The achievement can be completed alongside Immortal Raid Team.

name: Immortal Raid Team
description: Immortal Raid Team is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode raid without anyone dying.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Trio) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Trio) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (Trio) in under 35:00.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (5-scale) in under 30:00.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Solo) Speed-Chaser
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Solo) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (Solo) in under 45:00.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM Master
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode 10 times.

name: Moving Collateral
description: Moving Collateral is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana in a private instance without attacking her directly.

name: Corporeal Beast Master
description: Corporeal Beast Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corporeal Beast 50 times.

name: Perfect Corrupted Hunllef
description: Perfect Corrupted Hunllef is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corrupted Hunllef without taking damage from: Tornadoes, Damaging Floor or Stomp Attacks Also, do not take damage off prayer and do not attack the Corrupted Hunllef with the wrong weapon, within The Corrupted Gauntlet.

name: Defence Doesn't Matter II
description:
Defence Doesn't Matter II is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corrupted Hunllef without making any armour within The Corrupted Gauntlet.
Focus on increasing your dps by crafting a perfected bow and perfected staff, using Rigour and Augury, attacking while moving, and entering the fight with full health and prayer. You can maximize inventory space for food by decanting into 4-dose potions.

name: Corrupted Warrior
description:
Morrigan's coif (bh) is a piece of armour requiring 78 Defence to wear, and is purchased from the Bounty Hunter Store for 400 points. When worn alongside Morrigan's leather body (bh) and leather chaps (bh), the accuracy of ranged special attacks are increased by 15%. It can be converted into its corrupted variant by speaking to a Corrupted Warrior.
As with all Ancient Warriors' equipment from Bounty Hunter, it is initially purchased in inactive form and must be charged with 5,000,000 coins before it can be used by the...

name: Corrupted Gauntlet Speed-Chaser
description: Corrupted Gauntlet Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Corrupted Gauntlet in less than 7 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: Corrupted Gauntlet Master
description: Corrupted Gauntlet Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Corrupted Gauntlet 10 times.

name: Defence Doesn't Matter
description: Defence Doesn't Matter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without making any armour within The Gauntlet.

name: Perfect Crystalline Hunllef
description: Perfect Crystalline Hunllef is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Crystalline Hunllef without taking damage from: Tornadoes, Damaging Floor or the Hunllef's Stomp Attacks. Also, do not take damage off prayer and do not attack the Crystalline Hunllef with the wrong weapon, within The Gauntlet.

name: Gauntlet Master
description: Gauntlet Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Gauntlet 20 times. Completions of the Corrupted Gauntlet will also count towards this task.

name: Gauntlet Speed-Chaser
description: Gauntlet Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Gauntlet in less than 5 minutes.

name: Doom Chaser
description: Doom Crawler is an master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 in less than 10 minutes.

name: Mine's Better
description: Mine's Better is a master combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 with a shield always equipped.

name: Mokhaiotl Drift
description: Mokhaiotl Drift is a master combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 8+ before it finishes its first burrow phase.

name: Doom Veteran
description: Doom Veteran is a master combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 8.

name: Grub Patrol
description: Grub Patrol is a master combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 whilst never letting a Demonic larva be absorbed.

name: Perfect Duke Sucellus
description:
Perfect Duke Sucellus is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus five times within the same instance, without taking any avoidable damage.
Avoidable damage includes:

Melee attacks from his slam attack (the chip damage taken from the rising icicles are considered unavoidable)
Standard magic attack (praying against them will still fail the achievement, even when hit for a 0)
Damage from the Freezing Gaze attack
Damage from ignited gas vents in both the preparation and battle phases...

name: Duke Sucellus Master
description: Duke Sucellus Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus 50 times.

name: Duke Sucellus Speed-Chaser
description: Duke Sucellus Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus in under 50 seconds, without a slayer task.

name: Cold Feet
description: Cold Feet is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus while walking and taking zero avoidable damage.

name: One-off
description: Miniquests are groups of objectives that, unlike quests, have no icon on the world map and offer no quest points upon completion. There will also be no indication of starting nor completing a miniquest, other than what is written in the corresponding Quest List journal entry. There are a total of 19 miniquests, which are all members-only.

name: Colosseum Speed-Chaser
description: Colosseum Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fortis Colosseum with a total time of 28 minutes or less.

name: Showboating
description: Showboating is a master combat achievement which requires the player to use the Fortis Salute emote to the north, east, south, and west of the arena while Sol Heredit is below 10% of his hitpoints.

name: I Brought Mine Too
description:
The sunlight spear is a two-handed weapon that was a reward from completing all column 6 tasks in Grid Master. Every time the player attacks using the spear, they will gain a "Sunlight Stack", which can be stacked up to 20. Players will lose a Sunlight Stack if they have not attacked for 50 ticks (30 seconds). Additionally, teleporting will reset the Sunlight Stacks to zero.
Despite the name, the Sunlight Spear is considered a Stab Sword and will not complete the Combat Achievement I Brought Mine Too for killing Sol...

name: Sportsmanship
description: Sportsmanship is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sol Heredit once.

name: ... 'til Dawn
description: ... 'til Dawn is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians 20 times in a single trip.

name: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Chaser
description: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians in under 1 minute and 40 seconds.

name: Perfect Grotesque Guardians II
description:
Perfect Grotesque Guardians II is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians five times in a row without leaving the area, whilst satisfying the conditions for Perfect Grotesque Guardians.
This means the player must avoid the following:

Taking damage from Dusk's blinding attack.
Taking damage from Dusk's prison attack.
Taking damage from Dawn's rockfall attack.
Letting Dawn receive any healing from her orbs.
Being hit by any lightning attacks.
Letting Dusk use his prison attack...

name: Hespori Speed-Chaser
description: Hespori Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hespori in under 36 seconds.

name: One Hundred Tentacles
description: One Hundred Tentacles is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Kraken a hundred times in a single trip in an instance without leaving or logging out.

name: Collateral Damage
description: Collateral Damage is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra in a private instance without ever attacking him directly.

name: Swoop No More
description: Swoop No More is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra in a private instance without taking any melee damage from the boss or his bodyguards.

name: Perfect Leviathan
description:
Perfect Leviathan is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan five times without leaving and taking any avoidable damage.
Avoidable damage includes:

Standard rapid-fire volleys
Bite damage
Lightning Barrage damage
Smoke Blast damage (avoiding boulders and the blast itself)
Prayer-piercing damage during the enrage phase from being outside the range of the abyssal pathfinder
As the task's description implies, you must simply achieve 5 perfect kills in a single instance, rather than...

name: Leviathan Speed-Chaser
description: Leviathan Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan in under 1 minute and 25 seconds, without being on a slayer task.

name: Leviathan Master
description: Leviathan Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan 50 times.

name: Serpentine Solo
description: Serpentine Solo is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan without stunning it more than once with shadow spells.

name: A siphon will solve this
description: A siphon will solve this is a master combat achievement which requires players to kill Nex without letting her heal from her Blood Siphon special attack.

name: There is no escape!
description: There is no escape! is a master combat achievement which requires players to kill Nex without having anyone take damage from her Smoke Dash attack.

name: Contain this!
description: Contain this! is a master combat achievement which requires players to kill Nex without having anyone take damage from her Containment and Ice Prison attacks.

name: Nex Master
description: Nex Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex 25 times.

name: Nex Trio
description: Nex Trio is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Nex with three or less players inside the arena at the start of the fight.

name: Shadows Move...
description:
Shadows Move... is a master combat achievement which requires players to kill Nex without anyone being hit by her Shadow Smash attack.
Upon the shadows appearing beneath the player, they will have three ticks (1.8 seconds) to move out of it before they erupt and damage the player.

name: Essence Farmer
description: Essence Farmer is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah 10 times in one trip.

name: More than just a ranged weapon
wikiTitle: More than just a ranged weapon
description: More than just a ranged weapon is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah via the use of salamanders.

name: Phantom Muspah Master
description: Phantom Muspah Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah 50 times.

name: Phantom Muspah Speed-Chaser
description: Phantom Muspah Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah in less than 2 minutes without being on a Slayer task.

name: Walk Straight Pray True
description:
Walk Straight Pray True is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah without taking any avoidable damage during the fight.
Avoidable damage includes:

Lightning Cloud damage
Melee hits
Spike spawn damage
Spike walk-on damage
Magic damage
Off-prayer ranged hits
Does not include periodical chip damage through Ranged prayer.

name: Space is Tight
description: Space is Tight is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah whilst it is surrounded by spikes.

name: Dreamland Express
description: Dreamland Express is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Phosani's Nightmare without a sleepwalker reaching her during her desperation phase and damaging the player.

name: Phosani's Master
description: Phosani's Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare 5 times.

name: Phosani's Speedchaser
description: Phosani's Speedchaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare in under 7 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: I Would Simply React
description: I Would Simply React is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare without having it disable their prayers.

name: Crush Hour
description: Crush Hour is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare while killing every husk and parasite that appears in a single hit.

name: Precise Positioning
description:
Lum Lagoon lies at the mouth of the River Lum, between the Lumbridge Swamp and the Kharidian Desert. Several fishing spots can be found on its shores, as well as boats to Misthalin Manor and the Ruins of Unkah. It connects to the Lumbridge Basin to the west.
A stepping stone located at the mouth of Lum Lagoon serves as an Agility shortcut between the Lumbridge Swamp and Kharidian Desert, requiring 66 Agility to cross.
A Raft can easily pass the agility shortcut. It is difficult, but possible to pass in a Skiff with...

name: Is it a bird?
description: Is it a bird? is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl using only Dragonbane weapons. Only the player seeking the achievement must use dragonbane weapons; other players fighting the boss can use any gear.

name: Hueycoatl Speed-Chaser
description: Hueycoatl Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl in 2:30 with five or fewer players.

name: Perfect Nightmare
description: Perfect Nightmare is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Nightmare without any player taking damage from the following attacks: Nightmare rifts, an un-cured parasite explosion, Corpse flowers or the Nightmare's Surge. Also, no player can take damage off prayer or have their attacks slowed by the Nightmare spores.

name: Nightmare Master
description: Nightmare Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat The Nightmare 50 times. Phosani's Nightmare kills will also count towards this achievement.

name: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Chaser
description: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare, solo, in under 19 minutes.

name: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser
description: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare in a team of 5 players in under 4 minutes.

name: Theatre of Blood Master
description: Theatre of Blood Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood 75 times. Hard Mode Theatre of Blood completions will also count towards this achievement.

name: Perfect Xarpus
description: Perfect Xarpus is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Xarpus without taking any damage from his attacks and without letting an exhumed heal him more than two times.

name: Pop It
description: Pop It is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Verzik without any Nylocas being frozen and without anyone taking damage from the Nylocas and without dying yourself.

name: Can You Dance?
description: Can You Dance? is a master combat achievement requiring the player to kill Xarpus without anyone in the team using a ranged or magic weapon.

name: Perfect Bloat
description: Perfect Bloat is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Pestilent Bloat without anyone in the team taking damage from the following sources: Pestilent flies, Falling body parts or The Pestilent Bloats stomp attack.

name: Perfect Sotetseg
description: Perfect Sotetseg is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sotetseg without anyone in the team stepping on the wrong tile in the maze, without getting hit by the tornado and without taking any damage from Sotetseg's attacks whilst off prayer.

name: Back in My Day...
description: Back in My Day... is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Theatre of Blood raid without using a scythe of Vitur.

name: Can't Drain This
description: Can't Drain This is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Maiden of Sugadinti without losing any prayer points.

name: Theatre (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser
description: Theatre (5-Scale) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 5 players in less than 16 minutes.

name: Perfect Nylocas
description: Perfect Nylocas is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Nylocas Vasilias without anyone in the team attacking any Nylocas with the wrong attack style, without letting a pillar collapse and without getting hit by any of the Nylocas Vasilias attacks whilst off prayer.

name: Two-Down
description: Two-Down is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Pestilent Bloat before he shuts down a third time.

name: Perfect Verzik
description:
Perfect Verzik is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Verzik Vitur without anyone in the team taking avoidable damage from Verzik Vitur's attacks.
Specifically, players are not allowed to take damage from:

Magic and ranged attacks during phases 1 and 2
Damage from pillar falling
Nylocas explosions
Verzik's bounce attack during phase 2
If no damage is taken, this will not invalidate the run
Ranged or magic attacks during phase 3 that are not correctly prayed against
Being stuck in a web when...

name: Perfect Maiden
description: Perfect Maiden is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Maiden of Sugadinti without taking any damage off-prayer, from her blood splatter projectiles and Blood spawn trails along with letting a Nylocas Matomenos heal her.

name: Theatre (Trio) Speed-Chaser
description: Theatre (Trio) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of three players in less than 20 minutes.

name: Theatre (4-Scale) Speed-Chaser
description: Theatre (4-Scale) Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 4 players in less than 17 minutes.

name: A Timely Snack
description: A Timely Snack is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Sotetseg after taking at least 3 ball attacks without sharing the damage and without anyone dying in the fight.

name: Theatre of Blood: SM Speed-Chaser
description: Theatre of Blood: SM Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete an Entry Mode Theatre of Blood run within 17 minutes, not total completion time.

name: Hard Mode? Completed It
description: Hard Mode? Completed It is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode within the challenge time.

name: Perfect Kephri
description:
Perfect Kephri is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Kephri in an group of two or more players without taking any damage from egg explosions, her auto-attacks, exploding scarabs, bodyguards (chip damage from range and melee bodyguards does not disqualify if prayed against, neither does poison damage) and dung attacks, at raid level 150 or above. In addition, players must not let any Agile Scarabs hatch.
Unlike Perfect Ba-Ba, Perfect Akkha, and Perfect Zebak, this combat achievement does...

name: You are not prepared
description: You are not prepared is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid using only supplies provided by the Helpful Spirit without dying, at level 150 or above. The task will fail if any players in the raid use outside supplies.

name: Perfect Ba-Ba
description: Perfect Ba-Ba is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba in a group of two or more, at raid level 150 or above, without anyone taking any damage from the following: Ba-Ba's Attacks off-prayer, Ba-Ba's slam, rolling boulders, rubble attack or falling rocks. No sarcophagi may be opened. The player must have all Ba-Ba invocations activated.

name: Perfect Akkha
description: Perfect Akkha is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete Akkha in a group of two or more, without anyone taking any damage from the following: Akkha's attacks off-prayer, Akkha's special attacks (orbs, memory, detonate), exploding shadow timers, orbs in the enrage phase or attacking Akkha with the wrong style. The player must have all Akkha invocations activated.

name: Perfect Zebak
description: Perfect Zebak is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Zebak without taking any damage from incorrectly prayed attacks (excluding his blood magic), poison pools, blood spawns, and waves. All of his invocations must be activated to complete the task at raid level 150 or above.

name: Tomb Raider
description: Tomb Raider is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid 50 times, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Perfect Wardens
description: Perfect Wardens is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Wardens in a group of at least two players, while not taking damage from any avoidable attacks, while having all of their invocations enabled, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Chompington
description: Chompington is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Zebak using only melee attacks without dying, at raid level 150 or above. The achievement will be earned immediately after defeating Zebak so the raid does not need to be completed.

name: Tombs Speed Runner
description: Tombs Speed Runner is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid within 18 mins at any group size, at level 150 or above.

name: Better get movin'
description:
Better get movin' is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Elidinis' Warden in phase three of the Wardens fight with 'Aerial Assault', 'Stay vigilant' and 'Insanity' invocations activated, and without dying, at raid level 150 or above.
Completing the raid with the specified invocations, without fighting the correct warden in phase three, still yields in success.

name: Perfect Scabaras
description: Perfect Scabaras is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Path of Scabaras challenge room in less than a minute without anyone taking any damage from puzzles, at raid level 150 or above.

name: Tomb Looter
description: Tomb Looter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid 25 times, at level 150 or above.

name: Ba-Bananza
description:
Ba-Bananza is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Ba-Ba with all Ba-Ba invocations activated and the path levelled up to at least four, without dying. 
In solo, task is awarded even with multiple deaths, so it is recommended to set invocations to unlimited deaths, so that you can try repeatedly. Set invocations Walk the path and Pathmaster to have a chance to get room to level 4 as the second path. An invocation level of 300 is required to achieve the task, so it is recommended to pick remaining...

name: Rockin' around the croc
description: Rockin' around the croc is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Zebak at a path level of 4 with all invocations active without dying, at raid level 300 or above.

name: Doesn't bug me
description: Doesn't bug me is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Kephri with all invocations active, a path level of 4 and without dying at raid level 300 or above.

name: Expert Tomb Looter
description: Expert Tomb Looter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid 25 times, at level 300 or above.

name: Fancy feet
description: Fancy feet is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete phase three of The Wardens in a group of two or more, using only melee attacks and without dying, at raid level 300 or above. The 'Insanity' invocation must be activated.

name: All out of medics
description: All out of medics is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Kephri without letting her heal above 25% after the first down, without dying, at raid level 300 or above. The 'Medic' invocation must be activated. Any healing from the Soldier Scarab will not fail this task.

name: Resourceful Raider
description: Resourceful Raider is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid while having the "Dehydration" and "On a Diet" invocation on and no players dying, at level 300 or above.

name: Something of an expert myself
description: Something of an expert myself is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at level 350 or above without anyone dying.

name: Warden't you believe it
description: Warden't you believe it is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Wardens with all of their invocations active without dying, at raid level 300 or above.

name: But... Damage
description: But... Damage is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid without using any tier 75 or higher equipment, at level 300 or above.

name: Three Times the Thrashing
description: Three Times the Thrashing is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill three Tormented Demons within three seconds.

name: Supplies? Who Needs 'em?
description: Supplies? Who Needs 'em? is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's third challenge without having anything in their inventory.

name: Multi-Style Specialist
description: Multi-Style Specialist is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's third challenge while using a different attack style for each JalTok-Jad. The healers may be damaged with any combat style without failing the achievement.

name: Facing Jad Head-on IV
description: Facing Jad Head-on IV is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's fourth challenge with only melee.

name: The IV Jad Challenge
description: The IV Jad Challenge is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's fourth challenge.

name: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Chaser
description: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's third challenge in less than 3 minutes.

name: Nibblers, Begone!
description: Nibblers, Begone! is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk while not letting any of the three pillars that are provided at the start of the fight be destroyed by the Jal-Nibs.

name: Denying the Healers
description: Denying the Healers is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the TzHaar Fight Cave without letting any of the Yt-MejKot heal themselves or any other monster.

name: Fight Caves Master
description: Fight Caves Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves 5 times.

name: Fight Caves Speed-Chaser
description: Fight Caves Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves in less than 30 minutes.

name: You Didn't Say Anything About a Bat
wikiTitle: You Didn't Say Anything About a Bat
description: You Didn't Say Anything About a Bat is a master combat achievement which requires the player to complete the TzHaar Fight Caves without being attacked by a Tz-Kih.

name: Budget Cutter
description: Budget Cutter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis in combat equipment worth under 2,000,000.

name: Vardorvis Master
description: Vardorvis Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis 50 times.

name: Perfect Vardorvis
description:
Perfect Vardorvis is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis five times within the same instance, without taking any avoidable damage.
Avoidable damage includes:

Damage from a melee attack off-prayer
Damage from all special attacks
As the task's description implies, you must simply achieve 5 perfect kills in a single instance, rather than having to do so 5 kills in a row. This means that even if you achieve multiple perfect kills and fail before completing the task, you can continue...

name: Vardorvis Speed-Chaser
description: Vardorvis Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis in less than 1 minute and 5 seconds without a slayer task.

name: Vorkath Speed-Chaser
description: Vorkath Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath in less than 1 minute and 15 seconds.

name: Extended Encounter
description: Extended Encounter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath 10 times without leaving his area.

name: The Walk
description:
The Walk is a master combat achievement which requires the player to hit Vorkath 12 times during the acid special without getting hit by his rapid fire or the acid pools.
Completion of this achievement is calculated per acid phase, not per fight. As such, failing once does not prevent the player from attempting again during the same fight. Every attack counts towards the required 12; they do not need to deal damage.

name: Dodging the Dragon
description: Dodging the Dragon is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath 5 times without taking any damage from his special attacks and without leaving his area.

name: Vorkath Master
description: Vorkath Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath 100 times.

name: Perfect Whisperer
description:
Perfect Whisperer is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer five times within the same instance, without taking any avoidable damage.
Avoidable damage includes:

Any damage from her ranged, magic, and melee attacks. Only unprotected melee attacks will fail the achievement.
Getting hit by her tentacles.
Getting hit by her Screech attack.
Getting hit by her Soul Siphon attack.
Stepping on a dark green corrupted seed.
Any corrupted seeds being hatched.
As the task's description implies...

name: Whisperer Speed-Chaser
description: Whisperer Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer in less than 2 minutes and 25 seconds without being on a slayer task.

name: Whisperer Master
description: Whisperer Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer 50 times.

name: Yama Veteran
description: Yama Veteran is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama 50 times.

name: Yama Speed-Chaser
description: Yama Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama in an average time of under 3:00 over the player's most recent four kills.

name: Shadow dancer
description: Shadow dancer is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without getting hit by shadows and without being more than one tile away from the centre of his shadow crash attack.

name: No toppings, no drinks, thanks
description: No toppings, no drinks, thanks is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without anybody healing using anything other than plain pizza and without anybody drinking any potions.

name: Fire fighter
description: Fire fighter is a master combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without getting hit by fire and having only killed Void Flares with special attacks.

name: Zulrah Master
description: Zulrah Master is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah 150 times.

name: Zulrah Speed-Chaser
description: Zulrah Speed-Chaser is a master combat achievement requiring the player to kill Zulrah in less than 1 minute, without a slayer task.

name: Perfect Zulrah
description: Perfect Zulrah is a master combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah whilst taking no damage from the following: Snakelings, Venom Clouds, Zulrah's Green or Crimson phase.

name: Alchemical Speed-Runner
description:
The Alchemical Hydra is a boss version of hydra, found in the lower level of the Karuulm Slayer Dungeon in Mount Karuulm, requiring level 95 Slayer to kill. The Alchemical Hydra was the creation of a Dragonkin named Karuulm. While Karuulm saw promise in his creation, he nevertheless saw it as a failure because he could not replicate its traits, and abandoned it along with his other creations: the Wyrms, Drakes, and Hydras.
Unlike normal hydras, the Alchemical Hydra can only be killed while on a hydra Slayer task, of...

name: No Pressure
description: No Pressure is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Alchemical Hydra using only Dharok's greataxe as a weapon whilst having no more than 10 Hitpoints throughout the entire fight.

name: Swimming in Venom
description: Swimming in Venom is a grandmaster combat achievement requiring the player to kill Araxxor without having him move.

name: Perfect Araxxor 2
description:
Perfect Araxxor 2 is a grandmaster combat achievement requiring the player to perfectly kill Araxxor as well as never hitting him during his enrage phase.
Note: The failure message for Perfect Araxxor 2 will not appear if the player fails the conditions of Perfect Araxxor prior to the enrage phase. It is recommended to enable the repeat failure message for Combat Achievements in the settings interface to know if Perfect Araxxor was failed, which automatically disqualifies the player from Perfect Araxxor 2.

name: Araxxor Speed-Runner
description: Araxxor Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Araxxor 6 times within ten minutes. This task includes Araxxor's respawn time (9 seconds), thus essentially requiring an average time of 1:31 or less for each kill.

name: Chambers of Xeric (5-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Chambers of Xeric (5-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric (5-scale) in under 12:30.

name: Chambers of Xeric (Trio) Speed-Runner
description:
Chambers of Xeric (Trio) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric (Trio) in under 14:30.

Any raid layout with enough overload is doable by no-prepping, minimizing tick loss, staying overloaded, and using offensive prayers. Two overloads can be enough with a maximum of one iron: Everyone sips the first overload. One player, the iron if there is one, should pick up a Twisted(+) from Vanguards or Vasa for Olm head. Everyone sips the second overload. The...

name: Chambers of Xeric Grandmaster
description: Chambers of Xeric Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric 150 times.

name: Chambers of Xeric (Solo) Speed-Runner
description: Chambers of Xeric (Solo) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a solo Chambers of Xeric run in under 17 minutes.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Trio) Speed-Runner
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Trio) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (Trio) in under 27:00.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM Grandmaster
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode 25 times.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (5-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (5-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (5-scale) in under 25:00.

name: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Solo) Speed-Runner
description: Chambers of Xeric: CM (Solo) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Chambers of Xeric: Challenge Mode (Solo) in under 38:30.

name: Animal Whisperer
description: Animal Whisperer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana in a private instance without taking damage from either her or her bodyguards.

name: Peach Conjurer
description: Peach Conjurer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Commander Zilyana 50 times in a private instance, without leaving the room. In order to attempt this task, players will need to have the Hard Combat Achievements done so that they are able to rent private instances.

name: Egniol Diet II
description: Egniol Diet II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corrupted Hunllef without making an egniol potion within The Corrupted Gauntlet.

name: Corrupted Gauntlet Grandmaster
description: Corrupted Gauntlet Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Corrupted Gauntlet 50 times.

name: Wolf Puncher II
description: Wolf Puncher II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Corrupted Hunllef without making more than one attuned weapon, within The Corrupted Gauntlet.

name: Corrupted Gauntlet Speed-Runner
description: Corrupted Gauntlet Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Corrupted Gauntlet in less than 6 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: Gauntlet Speed-Runner
description: Gauntlet Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete The Gauntlet in less than 4 minutes.

name: Duel of Mokhaiotl
description:
Duel of Mokhaiotl is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8, whilst only damaging the boss with one-handed melee attacks.
Damaging the boss with grubs outside of shield phase will fail the achievement, however grubs that hit during shield phase will not. Damage from the Scorching bow or demonbane spells during the shield phase will fail the achievement.

name: Perfect Doom
description: Perfect Doom is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 without taking damage from the boss, letting any demonic larvae be absorbed, or stepping on acid blood.

name: The Praying Mantis
description: The Praying Mantis is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 8 without restoring any prayer points.

name: Doom Racer
description: Doom Racer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 in less than 7 minutes and 15 seconds.

name: Darkness Is Your Ally?
description: Darkness Is Your Ally? is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve levels 1 through 8 without equipping a demonbane weapon.

name: It's Dark Down Here
description: It's Dark Down Here is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires defeating the Doom of Mokhaiotl at delve level 16.

name: Mopping up
description:
Mopping Up is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires clearing eight or more acid blood with one earthen shield during the fight against the Doom of Mokhaiotl.
The achievement is completed as soon as the earthen shield clears any eight tiles with acid blood in them, rather than being completed upon defeating the Doom once the criteria is satisfied.

name: Duke Sucellus Sleeper
description: Duke Sucellus Sleeper is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill awakened Duke Sucellus once.

name: Mirror Image
description: Mirror Image is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus whilst only attacking the boss on the same tick that he attacks the player.

name: Duke Sucellus Speed-Runner
description: Duke Sucellus Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Duke Sucellus in less than 40 seconds, without being on a slayer task.

name: Reinforcements
description: Reinforcements is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sol Heredit with Bees II, Solarflare II and Quartet modifiers active.

name: Slow Dancing in the Sand
description: Slow Dancing in the Sand is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sol Heredit without running during the fight.

name: Perfect Footwork
description: Perfect Footwork is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sol Heredit without taking any damage from his Spear, Shield, Grapple, or Triple Attack.

name: Colosseum Speed-Runner
description: Colosseum Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fortis Colosseum with a total time of 24 minutes or less.

name: Colosseum Grand Champion
description: Colosseum Grand Champion is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sol Heredit 10 times.

name: Keep Away
description: Keep Away is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor in an instance without taking any damage from him or his bodyguards.

name: Defence Matters
description: Defence Matters is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor two consecutive times in one trip in a private instance without taking damage from his bodyguards.

name: Ourg Killer
description:
Ourg Killer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill General Graardor 15 times in a private instance without leaving the room.
In order to rent a private instance, the player must have the Hard Combat Achievements completed.

name: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Runner
description: Grotesque Guardians Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Grotesque Guardians in less than 1 minute and 20 seconds.

name: Demon Whisperer
description: Demon Whisperer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth in a private instance without ever being hit by his bodyguards.

name: Ash Collector
description: Ash Collector is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill K'ril Tsutsaroth 20 times in a private instance without leaving the room.

name: The Worst Ranged Weapon
description: The Worst Ranged Weapon is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra via damage inflicted by salamanders.

name: Feather Hunter
description: Feather Hunter is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Kree'arra 30 times in a private instance without leaving the room.

name: Leviathan Sleeper
description: Leviathan Sleeper is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the awakened Leviathan once.

name: Leviathan Speed-Runner
description: Leviathan Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan in less than 1 minute and 10 seconds, without being on a slayer task.

name: Unconventional
description: Unconventional is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Leviathan using only mithril ammunition whilst having no more than 25 Hitpoints throughout the entire fight.

name: Nex Duo
description:
Money making guide/Killing Nex may refer to:

Money making guide/Killing Nex (Team)
Money making guide/Killing Nex (Duo)

name: Perfect Nex
description:
Perfect Nex is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires players to kill Nex while qualifying for the completion of the following tasks: There is no escape!, Shadows Move..., A siphon will solve this, and Contain this!.
This means the player must kill Nex without anyone doing the following:

Taking damage from Nex's Smoke Dash, Shadow Smash, Containment, and Ice Prison attacks
Attacking Nex whilst she is performing her Blood Siphon attack
Despite being a grandmaster task, it can be attempted with any amount of...

name: I should see a doctor
description: I should see a doctor is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires players to get kill credit for Nex while a player is infected with Nex's Choke attack.

name: Phantom Muspah Speed-Runner
description: Phantom Muspah Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah in less than 1 minute and 30 seconds without being on a Slayer task.

name: Phantom Muspah Manipulator
description:
Phantom Muspah Manipulator is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Phantom Muspah whilst also completing the Walk Straight Pray True, Space is Tight, and Can't Escape tasks in the same kill. This means the player must do the following:

Have run energy turned off
Surround the boss with spikes during the last phase
Take no avoidable damage
Although the damage is calculated at the start of the projectile, not having Protect from Magic enabled when the corruption magic attack hits the...

name: Phosani's Grandmaster
description: Phosani's Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare 25 times.

name: Perfect Phosani's Nightmare
description: Perfect Phosani's Nightmare is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare while only taking damage from husks, weakened parasites and power blasts while also not getting slowed by spores or letting a sleepwalker reach her.

name: Can't Wake Up
description: Can't Wake Up is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare five times in a row without leaving her dream.

name: Phosani's Speedrunner
description: Phosani's Speedrunner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Phosani's Nightmare in under 6 minutes.

name: Hueycoatl Speed-Runner
description: Hueycoatl Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Hueycoatl in 2:30 with three or fewer players.

name: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Nightmare (5-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare in a team of 5 players in under 3 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: Terrible Parent
description: Terrible Parent is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill The Nightmare in a solo encounter without the Parasites healing her for over 100 health.

name: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Runner
description: Nightmare (Solo) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Nightmare in a solo encounter within 16 minutes.

name: A Long Trip
description: A Long Trip is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires The Nightmare to be defeated with all players in the fight not losing any prayer points.

name: Theatre (Duo) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre (Duo) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 2 players in less than 26 minutes.

name: Theatre (Trio) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre (Trio) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 3 players in less than 17 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: Morytania Only
description: Morytania Only is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Theatre of Blood run without using a non-Barrows brothers weapon, barring the Dawnbringer.

name: Perfect Theatre
description: Perfect Theatre is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood without anyone dying while qualifying for the completion of Perfect Maiden, Perfect Bloat, Perfect Nylocas, Perfect Sotetseg, Perfect Xarpus, and Perfect Verzik.

name: Theatre (4-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre (4-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 4 players in less than 15 minutes.

name: Theatre (5-Scale) Speed-Runner
description:
Theatre (5-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood in a team of 5 players in less than 14 minutes and 15 seconds.
Unlike Tombs of Amascut, speed-based achievements for the Theatre of Blood count the challenge time rather than the overall time.

name: Theatre of Blood Grandmaster
description: Theatre of Blood Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood 150 times. Hard Mode Theatre of Blood completions will also count towards this achievement.

name: Theatre: HM (4-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre: HM (4-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode in a team of 4 players with an overall time of less than 21 minutes.

name: Harder Mode II
description: Harder Mode II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Xarpus in hard mode after letting the exhumed heal him to full and without anyone taking any damage from him.

name: Nylo Sniper
description: Nylo Sniper is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Verzik Vitur in a Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode run without letting a nylocas explode during the fight.

name: Theatre: HM (5-Scale) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre: HM (5-Scale) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode in a team of 5 players with an overall time of less than 19 minutes.

name: Theatre: HM (Trio) Speed-Runner
description: Theatre: HM (Trio) Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode in a team of 3 players with an overall time of less than 23 minutes.

name: Theatre of Blood: HM Grandmaster
description: Theatre of Blood: HM Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode 50 times.

name: Personal Space
description: Personal Space is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat the Pestilent Bloat, in hard mode, with at least three players in the room and without any of them standing on top of each other.

name: Pack Like a Yak
description: Pack Like a Yak is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode raid within the challenge time, without anyone dying and without buying anything from the supply chest.

name: Stop Right There!
description: Stop Right There! is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat The Maiden of Sugadinti in hard mode without letting her blood spawns create more than 15 trails of blood.

name: Team Work Makes the Dream Work
wikiTitle: Team Work Makes the Dream Work
description: Team Work Makes the Dream Work is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to have everyone get through the attack without taking damage when Verzik Vitur, in the Theatre of Blood: Hard Mode, uses her yellow power blast attack while the tornadoes are active. This cannot be completed with one player alive.

name: Harder Mode I
description: Harder Mode I is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Sotetseg in hard mode, without taking any damage from its attacks, sharing the large red ball damage, stepping on the wrong tile in the maze, and dying.

name: Royal Affairs
description: Royal Affairs is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Nylocas room without dying in hard mode without letting a Nylocas Prinkipas change styles.

name: Harder Mode III
description: Harder Mode III is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Verzik Vitur in hard mode without using melee weapons during her third phase.

name: Perfection of Apmeken
description: Perfection of Apmeken is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete Perfect Apmeken and Perfect Ba-Ba in a single run of the Tombs of Amascut raid at raid level 300 or above.

name: Perfection of Crondis
description: Perfection of Crondis is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete Perfect Crondis and Perfect Zebak in a single run of the Tombs of Amascut raid at raid level 300 or above.

name: Perfection of Scabaras
description: Perfection of Scabaras is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete Perfect Scabaras and Perfect Kephri in a single Expert mode run of the Tombs of Amascut raid.

name: Perfection of Het
description: Perfection of Het is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete Perfect Het and Perfect Akkha in a single run of the Tombs of Amascut raid at raid level 300 or above.

name: Akkhan't Do it
description: Akkhan't Do it is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Akkha with all Akkha invocations activated and the path levelled up to at least four, without dying, at raid level 300 or above. Note that dying and resetting the fight allows multiple retries of this achievement.

name: Expert Tomb Raider
description: Expert Tomb Raider is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid 50 times, at level 300 or above.

name: Tombs Speed Runner II
description:
Tombs Speed Runner II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid within 20 minutes, with any group size, at level 300 or above.
This task is usually not done directly, instead, at the same time as Tombs Speed Runner III, as completing that task will satisfy this task. However, with strong enough gear and experience, this task can be easily completed on its own at a 300 raid level.

Hit 300 raid level while not using any path invocations, do use a 25 minute timer...

name: All Praise Zebak
description: All Praise Zebak is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zebak without losing prayer points at raid level 300 or above, while also satisfying the requirements of Rockin' around the croc achievement.

name: Tombs Speed Runner III
description:
Tombs Speed Runner III is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid in an 8-man party within 18 minutes, at raid level 300 or above.
Unlike the Theatre of Blood, speed-based achievements for the Tombs of Amascut count the overall time rather than the challenge time.

name: Maybe I'm the boss.
description: Maybe I'm the boss. is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete a Tombs of Amascut raid with every single boss invocation activated and without anyone dying.

name: Amascut's Remnant
description: Amascut's Remnant is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tombs of Amascut raid at level 500 or above without anyone dying.

name: Insanity
description: Insanity is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete Perfect Wardens in the Tombs of Amascut raid at level 300 or above.

name: The VI Jad Challenge
description: The VI Jad Challenge is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's sixth challenge.

name: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Runner
description: TzHaar-Ket-Rak's Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's fifth challenge in less than 5 minutes.

name: It Wasn't a Fluke
description: It Wasn't a Fluke is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete TzHaar-Ket-Rak's fifth and sixth challenges back to back without failing. The fifth challenge must be completed before the sixth challenge otherwise it will not be completed.

name: Nibbler Chaser
description: Nibbler Chaser is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without casting any spells in the Inferno.

name: Jad? What Are You Doing Here?
wikiTitle: Jad? What Are You Doing Here?
description: Jad? What Are You Doing Here? is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without killing the JalTok-Jad which spawns during wave 69.

name: Playing with Jads
description: Playing with Jads is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete wave 68 of the Inferno within 30 seconds of the first JalTok-Jad dying.

name: Facing Jad Head-on II
description: Facing Jad Head-on II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without using any ranged and magic weapons before fighting him.

name: Wasn't Even Close
description: Wasn't Even Close is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without falling below 50 hitpoints at any point during the Inferno run.

name: No Luck Required
description: No Luck Required is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without being hit by him and not taking any damage from a JalTok-Jad.

name: The Floor Is Lava
description: The Floor Is Lava is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without letting Jal-ImKot dig during any wave in the Inferno.

name: Inferno Grandmaster
description: Inferno Grandmaster is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Inferno 5 times.

name: Budget Setup
description: Budget Setup is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill TzKal-Zuk without using a twisted bow for the entire Inferno run.

name: Inferno Speed-Runner
description: Inferno Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Inferno in less than 65 minutes.

name: Fight Caves Speed-Runner
description: Fight Caves Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves in less than 26 minutes and 30 seconds.

name: No Time for a Drink
description: No Time for a Drink is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Fight Caves without losing any prayer points.

name: Denying the Healers II
description: Denying the Healers II is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to complete the Tzhaar Fight Caves without TzTok-Jad being healed by a Yt-HurKot.

name: Vardorvis Sleeper
description: Vardorvis Sleeper is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill awakened Vardorvis once.

name: Vardorvis Speed-Runner
description: Vardorvis Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis in less than 55 seconds without being on a slayer task.

name: Axe Enthusiast
description: Axe Enthusiast is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vardorvis after surviving for 3 minutes during his enrage phase, whilst never leaving the central 25 tiles of the fight area.

name: Vorkath Speed-Runner
description: Vorkath Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath in less than 54 seconds.

name: Faithless Encounter
description: Faithless Encounter is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath without losing any prayer points.

name: The Fremennik Way
description: The Fremennik Way is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Vorkath without any weapons.

name: Whisperer Speed-Runner
description: Whisperer Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer in less than 2 minutes and 5 seconds without being on a slayer task.

name: Whispered
description: Whispered is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the awakened Whisperer once.

name: Dark Memories
description: Dark Memories is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill the Whisperer whilst spending less than six seconds in the Shadow Realm prior to her enrage phase.

name: Yama Speed-Runner
description: Yama Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama in an average time of under 2:34 over the player's most recent four kills.

name: Contractually Unbound
description: Contractually Unbound is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama under the elevated conditions of one of his non-standard contracts.

name: Contract Choreographer
description: Contract Choreographer is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to defeat Yama without taking avoidable damage whilst also completing the Shadow dancer, Fire fighter, and Back so soon? tasks in the same kill.

name: Zulrah Speed-Runner
description: Zulrah Speed-Runner is a grandmaster combat achievement which requires the player to kill Zulrah in less than 54 seconds without having it assigned as a slayer task.
